<paragraph id="8BAFAB03FF8C927CFF7BF9AA86CA8E32" blockId="7.[136,687,1585,1612]" box="[136,687,1585,1612]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<heading id="D0E71C6FFF8C927CFF7BF9AA86CA8E32" bold="true" box="[136,687,1585,1612]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFF7BF9AA86CA8E32" bold="true" box="[136,687,1585,1612]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF8C927CFF57F9AA85E88E35" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[164,397,1585,1612]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFF57F9AA85E88E35" bold="true" box="[164,397,1585,1612]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Kalanchoe peltigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF8C927CFE3BF9A986CA8E32" authorityName=", Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" authorityYear="1949" box="[456,687,1585,1612]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFE3BF9A986458E32" bold="true" box="[456,544,1585,1612]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">K. rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFDA8F9AA86CA8E32" bold="true" box="[603,687,1585,1611]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30AF888FF8C9273FF7BF9E985128B8A" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAFAB03FF8C927CFF7BF9E9866E8E8D" blockId="7.[136,1452,1649,2091]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
We conclude that there are no material differences between the specimen, 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFC46F9E980498EF5" box="[949,1068,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Seyrig 819</emphasis>
, which was cited in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF8C927CFF55F90E868C8ED7" authority="(Boiteau &amp; Mannoni 1949: 71)" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityPageNumber="71" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[166,745,1684,1711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFF55F90E84988ED7" box="[166,253,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">K. rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFEC7F90E85ED8ED7" box="[308,392,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">seyrigii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF81D6F2FF8C927CFE65F90F86848ED7" author="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O." box="[406,737,1684,1710]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" pagination="69 - 76" refId="ref9125" refString="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O. (1949 [juillet-septembre]) Les Kalanchoe (suite). [ยง 7. Suffrutescentes.] (a suivre). Cactus (Paris) 1949 (21): 69 - 76, six unnumbered figures. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 12538078.2004.10516038" type="journal article" year="1949">Boiteau &amp; Mannoni 1949: 71</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and material from which the 
<typeStatus id="54AB15A1FF8C927CFBC0F90E80068ED6" box="[1075,1123,1685,1711]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF8C927CFB07F90E811C8ED7" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[1268,1401,1684,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFB07F90E811C8ED7" box="[1268,1401,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">K. peltigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was prepared. The 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFED9F92C85C78EA8" box="[298,418,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
Seyrig 
<specimenCount id="9D16608AFF8C927CFE8BF92C85C78EA8" box="[376,418,1719,1745]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" type="generic">819</specimenCount>
</emphasis>
specimen also closely coincides with the description included in the protologue of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF8C927CFF7BF94186628E8D" authority="(Descoings 2005 a: 6)" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityPageNumber="6" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[136,519,1753,1780]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFF7BF941856B8E8A" box="[136,270,1753,1779]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">K. peltigera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF81D6F2FF8C927CFEEFF94285988E8D" author="Descoings, B." box="[284,509,1753,1780]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" refId="ref9461" refString="Descoings, B. (2005 a) Crassulaceae madecassae novae. Societe Botanique de l'Ardeche (Ed.) Aubenas, 36 pp." type="book" year="2005">Descoings 2005a: 6</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFAB03FF8C927CFF4EF96785268052" blockId="7.[136,1452,1649,2091]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
Although some traits cannot be observed in 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFD36F96787248F6F" box="[709,833,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Seyrig 819</emphasis>
, these concern only colour and measurements of the internal floral structures, the latter at any rate being limited by the overall flower size, which has been shown to be a match between the taxa. The original description provided for 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF8C927CFCC6F8D980768F22" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[821,1043,1858,1884]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFCC6F8D987EE8F22" box="[821,907,1858,1883]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">K. rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFC4CF8D980768F22" box="[959,1043,1858,1883]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF81D6F2FF8C927CFBCAF8DA81038F25" author="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O." box="[1081,1382,1857,1884]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" pagination="69 - 76" refId="ref9125" refString="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O. (1949 [juillet-septembre]) Les Kalanchoe (suite). [ยง 7. Suffrutescentes.] (a suivre). Cactus (Paris) 1949 (21): 69 - 76, six unnumbered figures. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 12538078.2004.10516038" type="journal article" year="1949">Boiteau &amp; Mannoni (1949)</bibRefCitation>
based on their citation of 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFE97F8FF85BB8F07" box="[356,478,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Seyrig 819</emphasis>
confirms that the measurements of the androecium and gynoecium and other internal floral morphological structures, too, coincide with those applicable to 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF8C927CFC6EF81380468FD8" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[925,1059,1927,1953]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFC6EF81380468FD8" box="[925,1059,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">K. peltigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additional support is provided by the close geographical proximity (about 
<quantity id="4CE806E6FF8C927CFDA2F83286FE8FBD" box="[593,667,1961,1988]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" unit="km" value="50.0">50 km</quantity>
) of the localities from which 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFC19F83180068FBD" box="[1002,1123,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Seyrig 819</emphasis>
and the material from which the 
<typeStatus id="54AB15A1FF8C927CFF43F85684858F9E" box="[176,224,1997,2023]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF8C927CFE9CF85685918F9F" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[367,500,1996,2022]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFE9CF85685918F9F" box="[367,500,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">K. peltigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was prepared, originated. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFCE9F85787F78F9F" box="[794,914,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Seyrig 819</emphasis>
is therefore coextensive with material described as 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF8C927CFF54F86B85488070" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[167,301,2031,2057]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF8C927CFF54F86B85488070" box="[167,301,2031,2057]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">K. peltigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This specimen represents the earliest documented occurrence of the species and the earliest available herbarium sheet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFAB03FF839273FF4EFF05867088A2" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,1011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FF4EFF0585C688C1" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[189,419,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FF4EFF0585C688C1" box="[189,419,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Kalanchoe peltigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a unique species and we agree with 
<bibRefCitation id="EF81D6F2FF839273FCA7FF05804288C0" author="Descoings, B." box="[852,1063,158,185]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" refId="ref9461" refString="Descoings, B. (2005 a) Crassulaceae madecassae novae. Societe Botanique de l'Ardeche (Ed.) Aubenas, 36 pp." type="book" year="2005">Descoings (2005a)</bibRefCitation>
that it represents a combination of characters that warrant recognition.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFAB03FF839273FF4EFF7E878289CA" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,1011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
In the horticultural industry the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FD90FF7D87208886" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[611,837,229,255]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FD90FF7D86DF8886" box="[611,698,230,255]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FD02FF7D87208886" box="[753,837,230,255]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is often used to refer to a range of taxa that historically have been associated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FE42FE91866D895A" authorityName="Raymond-Hamet &amp; Perrier de la Bathie" authorityYear="1914" box="[433,520,266,291]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rosei">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FE42FE91866D895A" box="[433,520,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In such instances, this name is most often correctly associated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FAF4FE918563893E" authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Humbert" baseAuthorityYear="1933" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rosei" subSpecies="serratifolia">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FAF4FE91813B895A" box="[1287,1374,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FF7BFEB68563893E" box="[136,262,301,327]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">serratifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as the names are based on the same 
<typeStatus id="54AB15A1FF839273FD4EFEB68695893E" box="[701,752,301,327]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
, 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FD0DFEB587A2893E" box="[766,967,301,327]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">H. Humbert 5979</emphasis>
(see above), but also often confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FF7BFEC985C48912" authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Guillaumin &amp; Humbert" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[136,417,337,363]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rosei" subSpecies="variifolia">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FF7BFEC984848912" box="[136,225,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FECAFECA85C48912" box="[313,417,337,363]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">variifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Note though that the combination โ 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FCB2FEC980988912" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[833,1277,337,363]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" subSpecies="serratifolia" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FCB2FEC987FF8912" box="[833,922,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FC02FECA800A8912" box="[1009,1135,337,363]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">serratifolia</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FB5AFEC980988912" box="[1193,1277,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
โ, which is also sometimes encountered has not been validly published, and that 
<bibRefCitation id="EF81D6F2FF839273FCA6FEEE80D589F6" author="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O." box="[853,1200,373,399]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" pagination="69 - 76" refId="ref9125" refString="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O. (1949 [juillet-septembre]) Les Kalanchoe (suite). [ยง 7. Suffrutescentes.] (a suivre). Cactus (Paris) 1949 (21): 69 - 76, six unnumbered figures. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 12538078.2004.10516038" type="journal article" year="1949">Boiteau &amp; Mannoni (1949: 71)</bibRefCitation>
originally described it under 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FF3CFE0185D789CA" authority="subsp. rosei" box="[207,434,409,435]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rosei" subSpecies="rosei">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FF3CFE01854389CA" box="[207,294,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FE88FE0185D789CA" box="[379,434,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">rosei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FE2BFE01872389CA" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[472,838,409,435]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" subSpecies="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FE2BFE01864A89CA" box="[472,559,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FD77FE0186DE89CA" box="[644,699,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FD01FE01872389CA" box="[754,838,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as โ 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FC8DFE0287A889CA" box="[894,973,409,435]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Seyrigi</emphasis>
โ).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFAB03FF839273FF4EFE2681398AD6" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,1011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
In his compilation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FE4CFE26865D89AE" authorityName="Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[447,568,445,471]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FE4CFE26865D89AE" box="[447,568,445,471]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cultivars, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF81D6F2FF839273FD45FE26871C89AE" author="Shaw, J. M. H." box="[694,889,445,471]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" pagination="17 - 79" refId="ref10678" refString="Shaw, J. M. H. (2008) An investigation of the cultivated Kalanchoe daigremontiana group, with a checklist of Kalanchoe cultivars. Hanburyana 3: 17 - 79." type="journal article" year="2008">Shaw (2008: 73)</bibRefCitation>
refers to [
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FC0AFE25806989AE" box="[1017,1036,446,471]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K</emphasis>
.] โSeyrigiiโ under โSp. 30โ, i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FA61FE2584DA8982" authorityName="Raymond-Hamet &amp; Perrier de la Bathie" authorityYear="1914" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rosei">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FA61FE2584DA8982" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and cites โ[
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FEA2FE7985018982" box="[337,356,482,507]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K</emphasis>
.] 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FE8EFE7986268982" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[381,579,481,507]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FE8EFE7985D18982" box="[381,436,482,507]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FE1CFE7986268982" box="[495,579,482,507]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
โ as the โSyn. / Groupโ, with โ 
<bibRefCitation id="EF81D6F2FF839273FC51FE7A800A8982" author="Rauh, W." box="[930,1135,481,507]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" refId="ref10378" refString="Rauh, W. (1998) Succulent and xerophytic plants of Madagascar. Vol. 2 [of two volumes]. Strawberry Press, Mill Valley, California, 385 pp." type="book" year="1998">Rauh (1998: 323)</bibRefCitation>
โ and โGWโ, the website of Glasshouse Works, Church Street, PO Box 97, Stewart, 
<collectingRegion id="49D465E1FF839273FCF5FD9E875B8A66" box="[774,830,517,543]" country="United States of America" name="Ohio" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Ohio</collectingRegion>
45778-0097, 
<collectingCountry id="F307EB93FF839273FC2EFD9E80768A66" box="[989,1043,517,543]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">USA</collectingCountry>
(www.glasshouseworks.com) given as references for 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FEBAFDB185398A3A" box="[329,348,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K</emphasis>
. โSeyrigiiโ. Under 
<bibRefCitation id="EF81D6F2FF839273FDC2FDB287728A3A" author="Brickell, C. D. &amp; Alexander, C. &amp; Cubey, J. J. &amp; David, J. C. &amp; Hoffman, M. H. A. &amp; Leslie, A. C. &amp; Malecot, V. &amp; Xiaobai, Jin" box="[561,791,553,579]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref9185" refString="Brickell, C. D., Alexander, C., Cubey, J. J., David, J. C., Hoffman, M. H. A., Leslie, A. C., Malecot, V. &amp; Xiaobai, Jin. (2016 [June]) International code of nomenclature for cultivated plants (ICNCP or Cultivated Plant Code), incorporating the Rules and Recommendations for naming plants in cultivation adopted by the International Union of Biological Sciences and the International Commission for the Nomenclature of Cultivated Plants. 9 th Edn. International Society for Horticultural Science (ISHS), Leuven, Belgium. Scripta Horticulturae Number 18: 1 - 190." type="book chapter" year="2016">
Brickell 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FD61FDB186A18A3A" box="[658,708,553,579]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">et al</emphasis>
. (2016
</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 21.5), the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FBF8FDB1808B8A3A" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[1035,1262,553,579]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FBF8FDB180068A3A" box="[1035,1123,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FB69FDB1808B8A3A" box="[1178,1262,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, when treated as a cultivar, is to be written 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FE5DFDD586638A1E" authorityName="Raymond-Hamet &amp; Perrier de la Bathie" authorityYear="1914" box="[430,518,590,615]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rosei">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FE5DFDD586638A1E" box="[430,518,590,615]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
โSeyrigiiโ. 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FD74FDD687088A1E" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[647,877,589,615]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FD74FDD687088A1E" box="[647,877,589,615]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Kalanchoe peltigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as here circumscribed includes 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FB26FDD6812B8A1E" box="[1237,1358,589,615]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Seyrig 819</emphasis>
, but not other material previously attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FDC8FDE987458AF2" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[571,800,625,651]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FDC8FDE986F18AF2" box="[571,660,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FD3FFDE987458AF2" box="[716,800,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
such as that imaged at http://www.glasshouseworks.com/ kalanchoe-rosei-seyrigi?search= 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FE01FD0E860F8AD6" authorityName="Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[498,618,661,687]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Kalanchoe</taxonomicName>
under โ 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FD31FD0E871C8AD6" authorityName="Raymond-Hamet &amp; Perrier de la Bathie" authorityYear="1914" box="[706,889,661,687]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rosei">Kalanchoe rosei</taxonomicName>
seyrigi [spelled with one โiโ after the โgโ]โ.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFAB03FF839273FF4EFD2280238BFE" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,1011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
<bibRefCitation id="EF81D6F2FF839273FF4EFD2285E78AAA" author="Rauh, W." box="[189,386,697,723]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" refId="ref10378" refString="Rauh, W. (1998) Succulent and xerophytic plants of Madagascar. Vol. 2 [of two volumes]. Strawberry Press, Mill Valley, California, 385 pp." type="book" year="1998">Rauh (1998: 323)</bibRefCitation>
gave the following description for 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FCFFFD21878B8AAA" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[780,1006,697,723]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FCFFFD2187068AAA" box="[780,867,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FC69FD21878B8AAA" box="[922,1006,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which he ascribed to โMann. &amp; Boit.โ, i.e., Boiteau &amp; Mannoni, but in the opposite sequence: โLeaves lanceolate, 
<quantity id="4CE806E6FF839273FC08FD4680348A8E" box="[1019,1105,733,760]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" unit="cm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4โ5 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CE806E6FF839273FB6CFD4681658A8E" box="[1183,1280,733,760]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5โ6 mm</quantity>
wide, margins dentate-serrate. This 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FE87FC9A86778B62" box="[372,530,769,795]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" rank="variety" variety="occurs">variety occurs</taxonomicName>
between Bekily and Tsivoryโ. These traits describe 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FBAEFC9981248B62" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[1117,1345,769,795]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FBAEFC9980D08B62" box="[1117,1205,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FB1EFC9981248B62" box="[1261,1345,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on its 
<typeStatus id="54AB15A1FF839273FF5BFCBE84BD8B46" box="[168,216,805,831]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
material [โ 
<collectingRegion id="49D465E1FF839273FEA2FCBE85CD8B46" box="[337,424,805,831]" country="Madagascar" name="Toliara" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Toliara</collectingRegion>
, 
<quantity id="4CE806E6FF839273FE41FCBE86638B46" box="[434,518,805,832]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" unit="km" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4โ5 km</quantity>
north of Fort-Dauphin, towards the lagoon, max. 
<quantity id="4CE806E6FF839273FBDFFCBE80018B46" box="[1068,1124,805,832]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="25.0">25 m</quantity>
asl, 
<date id="FFAE8DC3FF839273FB66FCBE84A68B1A" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1928-09-20" valueMax="1928-10-06" valueMin="1928-09-20">20 Septemberโ6 October 1928</date>
, 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FF22FCD185F88B1A" box="[209,413,841,867]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">H. Humbert 5979</emphasis>
โ] which is from the Tolagnaro region instead. Only 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FBF5FCD180EA8B1A" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[1030,1167,841,867]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FBF5FCD180EA8B1A" box="[1030,1167,841,867]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. peltigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including the specimen 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FF7BFCF685648BFE" box="[136,257,877,903]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Seyrig 819</emphasis>
, occurs between Bekily and Tsivory (as discussed in โResultsโ, see 
<figureCitation id="132BB786FF839273FC07FCF6805C8BFE" box="[1012,1081,877,903]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,229,974,996]" captionTargetBox="[188,1403,206,937]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[177,1411,190,949]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Occurrences of specimens historically associated with K. rosei. ยฉ OpenStreetMap contributors." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5755764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5755764/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFAB03FF839273FF4EFC0A85128B8A" blockId="8.[136,1452,158,1011]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
At any rate, as discussed below under โTaxonomic affinities of 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FC9AFC0A80298BD2" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[873,1100,913,939]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FC9AFC0A80298BD2" box="[873,1100,913,939]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Kalanchoe peltigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
โ, 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FB97FC0980828BD2" baseAuthorityName="Descoings" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[1124,1255,913,939]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peltigera">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FB97FC0980828BD2" box="[1124,1255,913,939]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. peltigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not particularly closely related to either 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FE7CFC2D86E78BB6" authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Guillaumin &amp; Humbert" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[399,642,949,975]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="variifolia">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FE7CFC2D85838BB6" box="[399,486,950,975]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FDE9FC2E86E78BB6" box="[538,642,949,975]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">variifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or to 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FD33FC2D87FB8BB6" baseAuthorityName="Boiteau &amp; Mannoni" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[704,926,949,975]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="rosei" variety="seyrigii">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FD33FC2D87738BB6" box="[704,790,950,975]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FCB9FC2D87FB8BB6" box="[842,926,950,975]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">seyrigii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the correct name of 
<taxonomicName id="4C10D080FF839273FB76FC2D81CE8BB6" authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Humbert" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[1157,1451,949,975]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rosei" subSpecies="serratifolia">
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FB76FC2D80BE8BB6" box="[1157,1243,950,975]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">K. rosei</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B9647711FF839273FADEFC2E81CE8BB6" box="[1325,1451,949,975]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">serratifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the rank of variety.
</paragraph>
